34 E come, per lo natural costume, 35 le pole insieme, al cominciar del giorno, 36 si movono a scaldar le fredde piume;
37 poi altre vanno via sanza ritorno, 38 altre rivolgon sé onde son mosse, 39 e altre roteando fan soggiorno;
40 tal modo parve me che quivi fosse 41 in quello sfavillar che ’nsieme venne, 42 sì come in certo grado si percosse.

query.result:
**English:**
34 And just as, by natural instinct, 35 the magpies, together, at the beginning of the day, 36 move to warm their cold feathers;
37 then some go away without returning, 38 others turn back to where they were moved from, 39 and others, wheeling, remain;
40 in the same way it seemed to me that here 41 in that sparkling that came together, 42 they struck each other as if in a certain rank.
**Sanskrit:**
34 Evaṃ ca, svabhāvataḥ, 35 kākapakṣiṇaḥ, eka-sthitāḥ, divasa-ārambhe, 36 calanāḥ śīta-pakṣānāṃ tāpana-artham;
37 tataḥ anyāḥ gacchanti vinā nivṛttim, 38 anyāḥ āvartante yataḥ pravṛttāḥ, 39 anyāḥ āvartante sthitim kurvanti;
40 tathā-vidhaḥ prakāraḥ me abhūt atra 41 yasmin tad-dipyamāne yat eka-sthite ājagāma, 42 yathā niścite pade parasparam āhataḥ.

